Task 1: Daily cases

Data wrangling

reported <- reported_raw %>% 
  mutate_if(is.numeric, replace_na, replace = 0) %>%    
  mutate(reported_date = date(reported_date)) %>%    
  rename(Active = active, Recovered = recovered, Deceased = deceased) %>%   
  pivot_longer(-c(reported_date), 
               names_to = "status", values_to = "cases") %>%   
  mutate(status = fct_relevel(status, "Deceased", after = 2))

Data visualization

reported %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = reported_date, y = cases, fill = status)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Cases reported by day in Toronto, Canada",
       subtitle = "Confirmed and probable cases",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Case count",
       caption = str_c("Created by: Ivy Liang for STA303/1002, U of T\n",
                       "Source: Ontario Ministry of Health, Integrated Public Health Information System and CORES\n",
                       date_daily[1,1])) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(), legend.position = c(0.15,0.8)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(date("2020-01-01"), Sys.Date())) +
  scale_x_date(labels = scales::date_format("%d %b %y")) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(NA,2000)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Active" = "#003F5C", 
                               "Recovered" = "#86BCB6", 
                               "Deceased" = "#B9CA5D"))

Task 2: Outbreak type

Data wrangling

outbreak <- outbreak_raw %>% 
  mutate(episode_week = date(episode_week)) %>% 
  mutate(outbreak_or_sporadic = 
           str_replace(outbreak_or_sporadic, "OB Associated", "Outbreak associated")) %>% 
  group_by(episode_week) %>% 
  mutate(total_cases = sum(cases)) %>% 
  mutate(outbreak_or_sporadic = fct_relevel(outbreak_or_sporadic, "Sporadic", after = 1))

Data visualization

outbreak %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = episode_week, y = cases, fill = outbreak_or_sporadic)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(title = "Cases by outbreak type and week in Toronto, Canada",
       subtitle = "Confirmed and probable cases",
       x = "Date",
       y = "Case count",
       caption = str_c("Created by: Ivy Liang for STA303/1002, U of T\n",  
                       "Source: Ontario Ministry of Health, Integrated Public Health Information System and CORES\n",
                       date_daily[1,1])) +
  theme(legend.title = element_blank(), legend.position = c(0.15,0.8)) +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(date("2020-01-01"), Sys.Date() + 7)) +
  scale_x_date(labels = scales::date_format("%d %b %y")) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(0, max(outbreak$total_cases))) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("Sporadic" = "#86BCB6", 
                               "Outbreak associated" = "#B9CA5D"))

Task 3: Neighbourhoods

Data wrangling: part 1

income <- nbhood_profile %>% 
  filter(`_id` == 1143) %>% 
  pivot_longer(-c(`_id`, Category, Topic, `Data Source`, Characteristic), 
               names_to = "neighbourhood_name", values_to = "percentage") %>% 
  select(-c(`_id`, Category, Topic, `Data Source`, Characteristic)) %>% 
  mutate(percentage = parse_number(percentage)) %>% 
  mutate(neighbourhood_name = str_replace(neighbourhood_name, "Weston-Pelham", "Weston-Pellam"))

Data wrangling: part 2

nbhood_raw <- mutate(nbhood_raw, neighbourhood_name = 
                       str_replace(neighbourhood_name, "Weston-Pelham", "Weston-Pellam"))


nbhoods_all <- nbhoods_shape_raw %>% 
  mutate(neighbourhood_name = str_remove(AREA_NAME, "\\s\\(\\d+\\)$")) %>%  
  subset(neighbourhood_name != "city_of_toronto") %>%    
  mutate(neighbourhood_name = str_replace(neighbourhood_name, "St.James", "St. James")) %>% 
  right_join(nbhood_raw, by = "neighbourhood_name") %>%   
  right_join(income, by = "neighbourhood_name") %>%   
  rename(rate_per_100000 = rate_per_100_000_people) %>%    
  filter(!is.na(neighbourhood_id))

Data wrangling: part 3

nbhoods_final <- nbhoods_all %>% 
  mutate(med_inc = median(percentage)) %>% 
  mutate(med_rate = median(rate_per_100000))

nbhood_type <- c()

for (i in 1:140) {
  if(nbhoods_final$percentage[i] >= nbhoods_final$med_inc && 
     nbhoods_final$rate_per_100000[i] >= nbhoods_final$med_rate) {
    nbhood_type[i] <- "Higher low income rate, higher case rate"
  } else if (nbhoods_final$percentage[i] >= nbhoods_final$med_inc && 
             nbhoods_final$rate_per_100000[i] < nbhoods_final$med_rate) {
    nbhood_type[i] <- "Higher low income rate, lower case rate"
  } else if (nbhoods_final$percentage[i] < nbhoods_final$med_inc && 
             nbhoods_final$rate_per_100000[i] >= nbhoods_final$med_rate) {
    nbhood_type[i] <- "Lower low income rate, higher case rate"
  } else if (nbhoods_final$percentage[i] < nbhoods_final$med_inc && 
             nbhoods_final$rate_per_100000[i] < nbhoods_final$med_rate) {
    nbhood_type[i] <- "Lower low income rate, lower case rate"
  }
}

nbhood_type = fct_relevel(nbhood_type, "Lower low income rate, lower case rate", after = 3)

Data visualization

ggplot(data = nbhoods_final) + 
  geom_sf(aes(fill = percentage)) + 
  theme_map() +
  theme(legend.position = "right") + 
  scale_fill_gradient(name= "% low income", low = "darkgreen", high = "lightgrey") + 
  labs(title = "Percentage of 18 to 64 year olds living in a low income family (2015)",
       subtitle = "Neighbourhoods of Toronto, Canada",
       caption = str_c("Created by: Ivy Liang for STA303/1002, U of T\n",  
                       "Source: Census Profile 98-316-X2016001 via OpenData Toronto\n",
                       date_daily[1,1])) 

ggplot(data = nbhoods_final) + 
  geom_sf(aes(fill = rate_per_100000)) + 
  theme_map() +
  theme(legend.position = "right") + 
  scale_fill_gradient(name= "Cases per 100,000 people", low = "white", high = "darkorange") + 
  labs(title = "COVID-19 cases per 100,000, by neighbourhood in Toronto, Canada",
       caption = str_c("Created by: Ivy Liang for STA303/1002, U of T\n",  
                       "Source: Ontario Ministry of Health, Integrated Public Health Information System and CORES\n",
                       date_daily[1,1])) 

ggplot(data = nbhoods_final) + 
  geom_sf(aes(fill = nbhood_type)) + 
  theme_map() +
  theme(legend.position = "right") + 
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") + 
  labs(title = "COVID-19 cases per 100,000, by neighbourhood in Toronto, Canada",
       fill = "% of 18 to 64 year-olds in \nlow income families and \nCOVID-19 case rates",
       caption = str_c("Created by: Ivy Liang for STA303/1002, U of T\n",
                       "Income data source: Census Profile 98-316-X2916001 via OpenData Toronto
                       COVID data source: Ontario Ministry of Health, Integrated Public
                       Health Information System and CORES\n",
                       date_daily[1,1]))
